{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For knowledge augmentation, previous works (Guu et al., 2020; Yamada et al., 2020; Borgeaud et al., 2022) show performance improvements on knowledgeintensive tasks.",
    "Zhang et al. (2019) utilize both large-scale corpora and knowledge graphs to train a language model and take full advantage of various knowledge simultaneously.",
    "Qin et al. (2021) proposes a novel contrastive learning framework to obtain a deep understanding of the entities and their relations in text.",
    "Similarly, later works (Lewis et al., 2020; Kang et al., 2022; Li et al., 2022; Izacard et al., 2022; Chae et al., 2023) augment LMs with external knowledge during fine-tuning.",
    "However, they lack in generalization ability across different domains, and require changing model architectures or additional training steps on each task and dataset."
  ],
